        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Once the initial "WHOA! How much Str and Sta did you just give me???" factor of Degeneration wears off, most melees prefer Crippling Claudication I think, especially monks and rogues. There is almost certainly no doubt that an additional 50 Atk improves damage. Only question might be whether the improved DPS makes fights noticeably quicker for the mana expenditure. Anyway, it's not difficult to throw down 2 dots before casting CC, which will then last long enough for 2 more fights in an xp group. Degeneration is less useful because there's almost always someone in the group that can buff a tank up to max Str (and I'm not sure whether it blocks any Sta buffs).</P><P>My clerics have definitely noticed the effect of Zevfeer's and love it. It really saves them mana. Occasionally, they actually prefer it over Mind Wrack.</P><P>Tenaiya Soulscorcher</font></td>
