        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> When you're grouped, odds are the mob will die too fast for your dot to last its full duration. These taps were "supposed" to make us more group friendly without increasing our solo capabilities. They won't allow us to replace a shaman, or an enchanter or what have you. (I'm speaking in a general sense here, undead slows and screaming terror's situational uses aside.)</P><P>Their duration is absolutely annoying. The group taps wouldn't be so bad if they lasted longer. As is, they simply don't justify keeping them memmed, and having to mem-cycle them throughout gameplay because I'd rather keep much more usefull spells memmed has already made my wrist hurt. I should sue them for carpal tunnel.</P><P>I've asked monks, paladins, warriors, rogues.. and they all like crippling claudication and degeneration. Succession of shadows seems to be crap.</P><P>They also supposedly debuff the mob, but I have sat there with my eyes glued to my screen trying to discern any difference in what the mob is hitting for. I think I'll duo with a melee and actually run a parse.</P><P>My other complaint with them is they seem to be worthless on end mobs. Our dots don't stack on them, and it seems I can't get these "debuffs" to land either.</P><P>Can a group of wizards chain cast their manaburns? I read somewhere that necros cannot chain their lifeburns... no dot stack, no lifeburn stack. Now we can't Fear PC players.. not that I've been able to land fear or st on a 60 warrior anyway. I'm ready to switch to a bard if they weren't so broken. :)</P><P><BR><img src="http://www.havocink.com/eq/sig_malys.jpg" border=0><BR><font size=1>Baron</font id=size1><BR>____________________<BR><font size=1><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61374" target="_blank">Malys Undying</a> | House Archon</font id=size1></font></td>
